WEBVTT

00:05.042 --> 00:06.792
Look at that move!
Look at that move!

00:10.897 --> 00:12.080
Take him, Jack.

00:12.082 --> 00:13.331
Ten seconds, Jack!

00:15.001 --> 00:16.218
Go!

00:23.427 --> 00:25.343
Yeah! Yeah!
Okay.

00:26.764 --> 00:28.930
All right, Jack!

00:30.000 --> 00:36.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:37.090 --> 00:38.523
Dad! Dad!

00:38.525 --> 00:39.908
Dad, did you see?

00:39.910 --> 00:41.476
Did you see?
Danny. Danny.

00:41.478 --> 00:43.078
Hey, hey! Yes!
That was great.

00:43.080 --> 00:44.362
You juked that guy so much,

00:44.364 --> 00:45.964
I think you left
his jockstrap in Astoria.

00:45.966 --> 00:47.632
I faked him left,
then took him right.

00:47.634 --> 00:49.167
You did just the way
we practiced, right?

00:49.169 --> 00:50.869
Good job.
Thanks for letting me borrow this.

00:50.871 --> 00:51.953
No, that's yours.
Really?

00:51.955 --> 00:53.238
Yeah, you keep it.
Oh, thanks.

00:53.240 --> 00:55.290
Okay, come on.
You shoot, you score, you win.

00:55.292 --> 00:56.875
Now let's go get
some ice cream.

00:56.877 --> 00:58.159
Ice cream!
Ice cream!

00:58.161 --> 00:59.611
Let's go.
Ice cream.

00:59.613 --> 01:01.713
Ice cream. Ice cream.
Ice cream!

01:03.850 --> 01:05.667
So, what was that back there?

01:05.669 --> 01:06.968
It was nothing.

01:06.970 --> 01:09.821
Really? 'Cause it didn't
look like nothing.

01:09.823 --> 01:11.406
We'll talk about it
tonight, okay?

01:11.408 --> 01:12.524
Yes, please.

01:12.526 --> 01:14.810
We will.
Okay.

01:18.180 --> 01:19.781
That rabbit's foot
looked familiar.

01:19.783 --> 01:22.367
Yeah, think you gave it to me
around the same age.

01:22.369 --> 01:24.402
Pretty sure I hit
a home run that day, too.

01:24.404 --> 01:26.204
I have a vague
recollection of that.

01:26.206 --> 01:27.405
Everything okay?

01:27.407 --> 01:29.074
Yeah.

01:29.076 --> 01:31.827
Grandpa's treating
everybody to ice cream.

01:31.829 --> 01:34.246
That's why we invite him.

01:50.596 --> 01:51.546
Hey, Reagan.

01:51.548 --> 01:52.881
Reagan.
Hi, Sarge.

01:52.883 --> 01:54.883
Just the man I'm looking for.
Come on, walk with me.

01:54.885 --> 01:56.768
Hey, if this is about me
getting a new partner,

01:56.770 --> 01:58.069
you can stop apologizing.

01:58.071 --> 01:59.321
I get it. It's time.

01:59.323 --> 02:01.072
As a matter of fact,
it is about your new partner.

02:01.074 --> 02:02.223
I wanted to
introduce you to him.

02:02.225 --> 02:03.358
Renzulli.

02:03.360 --> 02:04.526
I got to take care
of this.

02:04.528 --> 02:07.195
I'll... I'll get back to you.
Yeah.

02:08.281 --> 02:09.497
Yeah, boss.

02:09.500 --> 02:11.500
Get out of here.
I told them straight up,

02:11.502 --> 02:13.401
"Your collar, your puddle."
You know what I'm saying?

02:13.403 --> 02:15.253
It's a new slogan
of mine, I swear.

02:15.255 --> 02:16.671
That's a great story, man.

02:16.673 --> 02:18.290
Best part of
the story is,

02:18.292 --> 02:20.008
I returned the phone

02:20.010 --> 02:21.510
to the blonde.

02:21.512 --> 02:24.379
And when I did,
she thanked me...

02:24.381 --> 02:25.764
all night long.

02:25.766 --> 02:27.682
I kid you not.

02:27.684 --> 02:29.434
It had to be done.

02:29.436 --> 02:30.969
You know what I mean?

02:30.971 --> 02:32.571
Oh, that's so wrong.
Hey.

02:32.573 --> 02:34.189
Hey, we didn't meet.
I'm Vinny Cruz.

02:34.191 --> 02:35.307
Hey. Jamie Reagan.

02:35.309 --> 02:36.424
That was some story.

02:36.426 --> 02:38.360
Oh, yeah.
The, uh, 3-5 was a madhouse.

02:38.362 --> 02:40.946
You know, real busy,
but a lot of laughs.

02:40.948 --> 02:42.230
So you're down here now?

02:42.232 --> 02:44.699
I am-- transferred
to the Midtown Country Club,

02:44.701 --> 02:45.951
effective today.

02:45.953 --> 02:48.203
Well, we may not be
as busy as the 3-5, but, uh,

02:48.205 --> 02:49.955
we see our share
of the action, too, right, guys?

02:49.957 --> 02:51.540
I know.
I'm just busting chops, man.

02:51.542 --> 02:53.325
But it was real good
to meet you.

02:53.327 --> 02:54.326
Yeah, you, too. Welcome.

02:54.328 --> 02:55.443
All right.
Okay, good.

02:55.445 --> 02:56.444
You two guys met?

02:56.446 --> 02:57.796
Yeah.
Yeah. We did.

02:57.798 --> 02:59.464
All right, well,
let's make it official.

02:59.466 --> 03:00.966
By the power vested in me,

03:00.968 --> 03:03.552
I pronounce
the two of you partners.

03:03.554 --> 03:05.921
So...

03:05.923 --> 03:08.390
Thanks, Sarge.

03:15.147 --> 03:17.182
How's our little David Beckham?

03:17.184 --> 03:18.350
Uh, he's looking at getting

03:18.352 --> 03:20.018
an endorsement deal
for his jersey now.

03:20.020 --> 03:21.736
Oh, brother.

03:21.738 --> 03:23.438
What's next, a
contract extension?

03:23.440 --> 03:24.823
Oh, you wish.

03:24.825 --> 03:27.325
He's, uh, asking questions
about Victoria Beckham.

03:28.645 --> 03:30.445
Over my dead body.

03:30.447 --> 03:31.997
It was a joke, Mom.

03:33.950 --> 03:35.333
What are you up to?

03:35.335 --> 03:38.319
I'm saying yes to St. Victor's.

03:39.205 --> 03:41.539
Jumping right back
into the rat race, huh?

03:42.960 --> 03:45.677
Danny.

03:45.679 --> 03:47.929
It's just a couple of
shifts at the hospital.

03:47.931 --> 03:49.764
It's not like I'm
going to be working

03:49.766 --> 03:51.683
the arbitrage
desk at Goldman.

03:51.685 --> 03:54.519
I know, I know.

03:56.188 --> 04:00.842
Maybe you want to try out
your nurse's outfit right now?

04:00.844 --> 04:05.063
Watch a movie or...
whatever.

04:05.948 --> 04:07.348
Sounds good.

04:07.350 --> 04:08.817
Yeah?
Yeah.

04:08.819 --> 04:10.785
As soon as you tell
me what had you

04:10.787 --> 04:12.787
jumping out of your
boots at the game today.

04:14.741 --> 04:16.541
That was nothing.

04:16.543 --> 04:19.661
Come on, you know I don't like
to bring the job home.

04:19.663 --> 04:21.079
It's fine.

04:21.081 --> 04:22.914
So, everything's okay?

04:22.916 --> 04:25.166
Right as rain.

04:25.168 --> 04:26.701
- Hey, Sarge.
- Hey, guys.

04:26.703 --> 04:27.919
What do we got?

04:27.921 --> 04:29.203
Charles Zappa.

04:29.205 --> 04:32.057
Says a male black, early 20s,
wearing a white T-shirt,

04:32.059 --> 04:33.892
put a gun on him
and swiped his bag

04:33.894 --> 04:35.310
coming off the
number six train.

04:35.312 --> 04:36.478
Mr. Zappa.

04:36.480 --> 04:37.762
You, uh... you look
pretty winded.

04:37.764 --> 04:40.098
You chased a guy with a gun
all the way here?

04:40.100 --> 04:41.232
Yeah.

04:41.234 --> 04:43.217
Listen, my wallet and my laptop
are in that bag.

04:43.219 --> 04:44.402
My whole life's in that thing.

04:44.404 --> 04:46.321
He lost him when the perp
buzzed into this building.

04:46.323 --> 04:48.023
We gonna go knock
on some doors?

04:48.025 --> 04:49.941
Yeah. You, me and Reagan.

04:49.943 --> 04:51.409
Blake, I want you
in the alley

04:51.411 --> 04:53.061
around the back
in case this mutt squirts.

04:53.063 --> 04:54.162
Ten-four, Sarge.
Now, you--

04:54.164 --> 04:55.563
wait by the car,
okay, Mr. Zappa?

04:55.565 --> 04:56.915
Yes, sir.
All right, boys.

05:09.679 --> 05:11.513
Who's there?

05:11.515 --> 05:14.432
Come on. Who's there?

05:49.385 --> 05:50.835
Heads up around back.

05:50.837 --> 05:52.921
Heavy movement
on the second floor.

05:52.923 --> 05:54.806
Rear apartment.
We're moving in on it.

05:54.808 --> 05:56.891
Copy that.

06:08.470 --> 06:10.155
Police. Open up.

06:11.306 --> 06:13.024
Sarge, there he goes!

06:13.026 --> 06:14.359
He's on the move!

06:24.620 --> 06:26.254
Don't move! Don't move.

06:26.256 --> 06:28.423
We got him!
Cuff him.

06:28.425 --> 06:30.125
We got him.

06:31.627 --> 06:33.161
Got a gun.

06:33.163 --> 06:35.680
Oh, let me guess--
that ain't yours, huh?

06:37.134 --> 06:38.516
Stay with him.

06:38.518 --> 06:40.468
Put shots fired over the air.

06:40.470 --> 06:42.887
Attention, 10-13--
shots fired.

06:42.889 --> 06:45.223
What happened?

06:45.225 --> 06:47.609
I don't know. He just...
he just came out of nowhere.

06:47.611 --> 06:50.111
Who is he?
I don't know!

06:50.113 --> 06:52.197
12 George to Central--
we need a bus at the rear

06:52.199 --> 06:53.481
of our location forthwith.
All right, buddy.

06:53.483 --> 06:54.866
We got it.
We got it from here.

06:54.868 --> 06:56.117
I shot him.
What did I do?

06:56.119 --> 06:58.236
He's going to make it.
Is he going to make it?

06:58.238 --> 06:59.571
You're going to be
all right, okay?

06:59.573 --> 07:00.538
Just stay with me, okay?

07:00.540 --> 07:01.689
Oh, my God.

07:01.691 --> 07:03.408
Help's on the way.
Oh, my God.

07:03.410 --> 07:06.027
I didn't want to alarm you.

07:06.029 --> 07:08.413
This is probably nothing.

07:08.415 --> 07:09.831
Sorry, Danny.
It's not nothing

07:09.833 --> 07:11.883
when you almost shoot
the Minafos' cat.

07:11.885 --> 07:13.718
I got a video text message

07:13.720 --> 07:16.104
from a guy that I collared
years ago.

07:16.106 --> 07:17.972
Well, what'd it say?

07:18.808 --> 07:21.009
Take a look.

07:22.428 --> 07:24.512
Hey, Danny.

07:24.514 --> 07:26.431
It's me.

07:28.051 --> 07:30.384
Been a while.

07:30.386 --> 07:34.272
Eight years, four months
and three days,

07:34.274 --> 07:36.608
to be exact.

07:36.610 --> 07:38.860
Hope you've been thinking of me,

07:38.862 --> 07:42.330
'cause I've been thinking
a lot about you.

07:43.732 --> 07:45.450
Anyway...

07:45.452 --> 07:47.919
I just got out.

07:47.921 --> 07:53.124
And I'm looking forward
to seeing you very soon.

07:53.126 --> 07:54.575
Bye.

07:54.577 --> 07:57.011
Jesus, Danny.

07:58.464 --> 08:01.015
Who is that?

08:03.936 --> 08:06.437
Wait a minute.

08:06.439 --> 08:09.023
Is that Benjamin Walker?

08:13.095 --> 08:15.480
You always swore that everyone
you collared swears revenge,

08:15.482 --> 08:18.533
but none of them have the balls
to do it except for...

08:18.535 --> 08:21.119
Except for Benjamin Walker.

08:22.755 --> 08:24.489
And now he's out
and he's threatening you.

08:24.491 --> 08:26.040
Isn't that against the law?

08:27.126 --> 08:30.245
In the eyes of the law,
he did nothing; he said hello.

08:30.247 --> 08:31.246
And in your eyes?

08:31.248 --> 08:33.414
In my eyes...

08:33.416 --> 08:36.333
whoever said time
heals all wounds

08:36.336 --> 08:38.303
probably never did prison time.

08:38.304 --> 08:40.972
You think he's coming after you,
and you're scared, Danny.

08:40.974 --> 08:42.140
Oh, no, whoa.

08:42.142 --> 08:43.808
I... I didn't say all of that.

08:43.809 --> 08:46.978
Danny, listen to me
for a second, okay?

08:46.980 --> 08:50.464
We've been married for 15 years,
and you've been

08:50.466 --> 08:52.984
wearing the shield
for every single one of them.

08:52.986 --> 08:54.519
Now, I don't know
if you noticed,

08:54.521 --> 08:56.654
but that doesn't mean
I get to kick back

08:56.656 --> 08:57.939
and have my nails done

08:57.941 --> 09:00.141
while you bust through walls
taking down bad guys.

09:00.143 --> 09:03.244
That means the both of us have
about two decades on the job.

09:03.246 --> 09:05.146
I know.

09:05.148 --> 09:07.198
I'm stronger
than you think, Danny.

09:07.200 --> 09:09.200
Just tell me
what we're up against.

09:10.669 --> 09:13.705
I'm not scared.

09:15.374 --> 09:17.091
Just concerned.

09:20.546 --> 09:22.964
Very concerned.

09:25.720 --> 09:29.720
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Blue Bloods 3x01 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Family Business</font>
